ARTICLE.TITLE: Coco Rocha serves goddess vibes in stunning sheer looks as she hits the runway at LA Fashion Week
ARTICLE.TEXT:
Coco Rocha has recently been busy bouncing around from one fashion week to the next.

But the madness isn't over, as she made a quick trip to the West Coast this weekend for Los Angeles Fashion Week.

She served pure goddess vibes Sunday as she hung out backstage at the runway shows.

Goddess vibes: Coco Rocha served pure goddess vibes Sunday as she hung out backstage at Los Angeles Fashoin Week

The 31-year-old put on a stunning display as she showed some skin in a revealing sheer mint green dress.

The one-shoulder number was belted, featuring a thigh-high leg slit and a long open sleeve.

She hung out with the other models backstage as they went through hair and makeup.

Rocha took to her Instagram story before the show as she went through hair and makeup.

Mint beauty: The 31-year-old put on a stunning display as she showed some skin in a revealing sheer mint green dress

Showing skin: The one-shoulder number was belted, featuring a thigh-high leg slit and a long open sleeve

Serving beauty: Her glam look featured a bronze smokey eye and a damp hairstyle

Teamwork: She hung out with the other models backstage as they went through hair and makeup

She also posed with designer Michael Costello and model Valentina Sampaio backstage, as they sported all black for their pre-show looks.

Sampaio recently made history when she became Victoria's Secret's first openly transgender model.

Rocha dazzled on the runway in the mint green look at the Michael Costello Spring/Summer 2020 show.

Glam squad: Rocha took to her Instagram story before the show as she went through hair and makeup

Squad goals: She also posed with designer Michael Costello and model Valentina Sampaio backstage, as they sported all black for their pre-show looks

She also modeled a sheer blush number, which featured long sleeves with layered tulle shoulders and a floor-length skirt, also trimmed in layered tulle.

Sampaio also hit the runway, sporting a sheer nude dress, embellished with teal floral embroidery, featuring billowy sleeves trimmed in feathers.

The ladies walked arm-in-arm with Costello following the show, as he took a bow on the runway.
